
[1]sleigh

   SLEIGH, n. sla. [probably allied to sleek.] A vehicle moved on runners,
   and greatly used in America for transporting persons or goods on snow
   or ice. [This word the English write and pronounce sledge, and apply it
   to what we calla sled.]
